    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="390"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/1780½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                        Counselor for the Department of State</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lansing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Lansing</hi>: Thank you for letting me see
                        this.<note n="98" xml:id="d390fn1">Mr. Lansing had forwarded to President
                        Wilson a telegram from Mr. Daniel F. Kellogg, of New York, in which
                        arbitration of the <hi rend="italic">Lusitania</hi> case was suggested and
                        in which it was stated that “people here would be strongly adverse to any
                        government action that would make war possible on any grounds that have been
                        disclosed to date.” (File No. 763.72/1779½.)</note> I have no doubt that it
                    interprets a very large element of opinion in the country, but I do not think
                    that anything that we are doing would exclude temperate action.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
